From: Android Build Support Generator
Date: Wed, 1 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Android build support for CausalLM Application

This patch adds Android build support for the CausalLM Application introduced in PR #3344.
The patch includes JNI bindings, build scripts, and a complete Android application structure
similar to the existing ResnetJNI application.

Features:
- JNI interface for CausalLM models (Llama, Qwen3, Qwen3-MoE)
- Android application with UI for text generation
- Build scripts that integrate with existing package_android.sh
- Support for all CausalLM model types from PR #3344

Files added:
- Applications/Android/CausalLMJNI/ - Complete Android application
- Applications/Android/CausalLMJNI/app/src/main/jni/ - JNI implementation
- Applications/Android/CausalLMJNI/build_causallm_android.sh - Main build script

Usage:
1. Ensure Android NDK is installed and ANDROID_NDK is set
2. Run: cd Applications/Android/CausalLMJNI && ./build_causallm_android.sh
3. Install the generated APK and copy model files to device

The build process:
1. Calls tools/package_android.sh to build nntrainer for Android
2. Extracts dependencies to JNI directory
3. Builds JNI library using ndk-build
4. Optionally builds Android APK using gradle

Directory structure created:
Applications/Android/CausalLMJNI/
