└── README.md

JNI Interface:
- createCausalLMModel() - Initialize model from config path
- initializeModel() - Initialize model instance
- loadWeights() - Load model weights
- runInference() - Run text generation
- destroyModel() - Clean up resources

Android Application Features:
- Simple UI for text input and output
- Asynchronous model operations
- Error handling and logging
- Support for different model types

Build Requirements:
- Android NDK (ANDROID_NDK environment variable)
- Android SDK API level 30+
- Existing nntrainer build system
- CausalLM implementation from PR #3344

This patch enables Android developers to use CausalLM models in their applications
following the same pattern as other nntrainer Android applications.

